ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: "Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month."

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

End time of the actigraphy recording
Time zone (e.g. eastern time)
Data file 1
type of data file 1
Total number of unique awakenings during the sleep period (excludes final awakening)
Ratio of time spent asleep to total time in bed, with total time in bed including true sleep and waking episodes
The event name for which the data was collected
Day of the week
First Minute that the participant was identified as being in-bed (but not necessarily asleep)

ElementDescription: First Minute that the participant was identified as being asleep
Notes: Unless otherwise stated, all data is offset by 12 hours so that 00:00= noon;  23:59=11:59A

ElementDescription: First Minute that the participant was identified as being out-bed (but may have woken up prior to this)
Notes: Unless otherwise stated, all data is offset by 12 hours so that 00:00= noon;  23:59=11:59A

ElementDescription: First Minute that the participant was identified as being awake
Notes: Unless otherwise stated, all data is offset by 12 hours so that 00:00= noon;  23:59=11:59A

ElementDescription: Total time within the sleep window (including wake periods) as calculated by 30 second sleep record

Average Activity Count

Onset Latency: The length of time it takes to transition of wakefulness to sleep
Sleep Efficiency: Percentage of total time in bed that was actually spent asleep
Wake After Sleep Onset: The amount of time the participant was awake during the night
Percentage of time spent awake
Number of periods of segmented wake times
Number of minutes per segmented wake time
Number of minutes asleep after sleep onset
Percentage of time spent asleep
Number of periods of segmented sleep time
Number of minutes per segmented sleep time
Sleep Fragmentation: Percentage of epochs with y-axis greater than 0 + percent 1 minute sleep vs. all periods of sleep during the sleep period
Timepoint/visit label
Wake Time: The number of minutes awake after sleep onset
Sleep Duration: The number of minutes the participant was sleeping
Analysis Name
Interval Type
Interval Number

Percentage of time Offwrist

Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
